{% include 'adp-user-context' %}
{% assign nav_key = 'accounting' %}
{% assign page_title = 'Accounting Activities' %}
{% assign breadcrumbs = 'Dashboard|/dashboard · Service Delivery|/service-delivery · Accounting' %}
{% include 'adp-shell-open' %}
{% comment %}
  Accounting Activities & Compliance
  ----------------------------------
  Surfaces the day-to-day bookkeeping work the firm performs for each client:
  vouchers/entries (purchase, sales, receipts, payments, bank, journal),
  reconciliations (bank + GST purchase vs 2B), variance analysis & documents,
  GST (GSTR-2B report + variance vs books), TDS / 26AS / AIS and payroll
  (incl. ESI & PF).

  A visual process-flow stepper at the top of the Entries tab shows which
  stages are unlocked. Gating is informational only in the preview: a later
  stage is "locked" with a reason when its prerequisites have no posted data
  (e.g. GST stays locked until purchase & sales entries are posted).

  Role-aware:
   - Accountant : portfolio across all client companies
   - Firm Admin : own company only
   - Operator / Client : page not available (handled below)

  Backing Dataverse tables (to be created in solution/src):
   - adp_voucher          : purchase / sales / receipt / payment / bank / journal entry
   - adp_bankrecon        : bank reconciliation lines (book vs bank)
   - adp_gst2b            : GSTR-2B inward supply lines + match status vs books
   - adp_gstvariance      : per-section GST variance (ITC books vs 2B, 3B vs books)
   - adp_variancedoc      : supporting documents attached to variances
   - adp_tds              : TDS deduction register
   - adp_form26as         : Form 26AS entries (tax credit statement)
   - adp_ais              : Annual Information Statement entries
   - adp_payroll          : payroll run rows
   - adp_esi / adp_pf     : ESI & PF contribution registers

  The preview harness stubs these tables; see preview/preview.js.
{% endcomment %}

{% assign is_operator   = false %}
{% assign is_admin      = false %}
{% assign is_accountant = false %}
{% if adp_personagroup == 'operator'   %}{% assign is_operator   = true %}{% endif %}
{% if adp_personagroup == 'firmadmin'  %}{% assign is_admin      = true %}{% endif %}
{% if adp_personagroup == 'accountant' %}{% assign is_accountant = true %}{% endif %}
{% assign can_view = false %}
{% if is_accountant or is_admin %}{% assign can_view = true %}{% endif %}

{% unless can_view %}
  <section class="acc-page">
    <div class="placeholder">
      <strong>Accounting Activities is an internal delivery workspace.</strong><br/>
      It is available to <em>Accountants</em> and <em>Firm Admins</em>. Switch the role selector to preview it.
    </div>
  </section>
{% else %}

{% comment %} ==================== Data ==================== {% endcomment %}
{% fetchxml vouchers_query %}
<fetch version="1.0" output-format="xml-platform" mapping="logical" distinct="false" top="300">
  <entity name="adp_voucher">
    <attribute name="adp_voucherid" />
    <attribute name="adp_companyid" />
    <attribute name="adp_vouchertype" />
    <attribute name="adp_date" />
    <attribute name="adp_party" />
    <attribute name="adp_reference" />
    <attribute name="adp_amount" />
    <attribute name="adp_status" />
    <attribute name="adp_narration" />
    {% unless is_accountant %}
    <filter><condition attribute="adp_companyid" operator="eq" value="{{ adp_companyid }}" /></filter>
    {% endunless %}
    <order attribute="adp_date" descending="true" />
  </entity>
</fetch>
{% endfetchxml %}
{% assign vouchers = vouchers_query.results.entities %}

